<item>
            <title>[LU-13148] Interop: sanity test 56ra fails with &apos;&apos;/usr/bin/lfs find -size 0 -type f -lazy /mnt/lustre/d56ra.sanity&apos; should not send glimpse RPCs to OST&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13148</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We see sanity test_56ra fail for interop testing with&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 56ra: check lfs find -size -lazy works for data on OSTs =============================== 10:30:40 (1578652240)
 sanity test_56ra: @@@@@@ FAIL: &apos;/usr/bin/lfs find -size 0 -type f -lazy /mnt/lustre/d56ra.sanity&apos; should not send glimpse RPCs to OST 
  Trace dump:
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:5900:error()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:5398:test_56ra()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We see this for older servers running with newer client versions of Lustre:&lt;br/&gt;
2.10.8 servers/2.12.3.93 clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c6ea7aca-3461-11ea-bb75-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c6ea7aca-3461-11ea-bb75-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
2.11.0 servers/2.12.3.93 clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b612b98e-346a-11ea-b1e8-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b612b98e-346a-11ea-b1e8-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
2.12.2 servers/2.12.58.155 clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/acaa7aa0-f241-11e9-a0ba-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/acaa7aa0-f241-11e9-a0ba-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like this started on 27 SEPT 2019 with Lustre 2.12.58.81 clients/2.12.2 servers; &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/6022cbce-e1cf-11e9-add9-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/6022cbce-e1cf-11e9-add9-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Interop: when Lustre client is newer than servers</environment>
